sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Requestor as Issuing Authority / Requestor
    participant Intake as Legal Intake Channel
    participant Counsel as Legal Counsel
    participant Sec as Security Lead
    participant Ed as Editorial Standards Lead
    participant Platform as Platform Ops
    participant Custodian as Data Custodian
    participant Audit as Immutable Audit Log
    participant Exec as Executive Duty Officer

    Note over Requestor,Audit: High-level legal-demand workflow (illustrative only)

    Requestor->>Intake: Serve subpoena/order/warrant request
    Intake->>Audit: Log receipt event (timestamp, request ID, requester metadata)
    Intake->>Counsel: Route request + artifacts for validation

    Counsel->>Counsel: Validate authenticity, jurisdiction, scope, enforceability
    Counsel->>Audit: Log legal validation result + rationale

    alt Invalid / defective / overbroad
        Counsel->>Requestor: Reject, seek correction, or move to narrow/challenge
        Counsel->>Audit: Log challenge/rejection action
    else Potentially valid request
        Counsel->>Sec: Request data-map feasibility and minimization check
        Counsel->>Ed: Assess source-protection/editorial sensitivity
        Sec->>Audit: Log technical scope feasibility outcome
        Ed->>Audit: Log editorial risk assessment outcome

        alt Preserve only (hold)
            Counsel->>Platform: Issue scoped legal hold instruction (matter ID, scope, expiry review)
            Platform->>Custodian: Apply hold to specified records
            Custodian->>Audit: Log hold applied (scope hash, approver, time)
            Counsel->>Requestor: Confirm preservation per legal requirements
        else Compelled production
            Counsel->>Sec: Authorize minimal compliant extraction plan
            Sec->>Custodian: Execute scoped export workflow
            Custodian->>Audit: Log extraction chain-of-custody
            Custodian->>Counsel: Deliver encrypted package + manifest
            Counsel->>Counsel: Final privilege/source-protection review
            Counsel->>Requestor: Produce minimum required data (if compelled)
            Counsel->>Audit: Log production details + legal basis
        end
    end

    alt Notification legally permitted
        Counsel->>Ed: Approve source/user notification plan
        Ed->>Audit: Log notification decision + timeline
    else Gag/seal restrictions apply
        Counsel->>Audit: Log deferred-notification basis and review date
    end

    Counsel->>Exec: Provide case summary + residual risk
    Exec->>Audit: Record executive oversight acknowledgment

    Note over Intake,Audit: All privileged actions produce immutable audit events and periodic review entries.
